# frontend/.env.example
#
# Example environment variables for the Vite SPA.
#
# Notes:
# - The SPA has no server-side secrets. All public OIDC config is served by the
#   backend at GET /api/v1/public-config.
# - The Vite dev server proxies /api/v1 to the backend (see vite.config.ts).

# Vite dev server proxy target (used only by the dev server, not the browser).
# VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://localhost:8000

# Admin authorization
# Admin gating is handled entirely by the backend. The backend checks Authentik
# group membership using its own OIDC_ADMIN_GROUP_CLAIM / OIDC_ADMIN_GROUP_NAME
# settings and exposes the result as `is_admin` on the /me endpoint. The
# frontend reads that boolean to show or hide admin UI. No frontend env vars
# are needed for admin access control.
